<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-04-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-04-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="1552" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1552">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 723.2515/134.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Buenos Aires</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-04-12">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 12, 1910</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>I have learned from the British Minister that he and the French Chargé
                            d’Affaires have received instructions to offer their moral support to
                            the Argentine Republic in settling Chile-Peru dispute; and that he had
                            telegraphed said instructions to the British Legations at Santiago and
                            Rio de Janeiro. He asked if I had similar instructions. I replied by
                            referring him to the Department of State, Washington.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sherrill</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>